memory: My name is Lars Langenbach.
I am 20 years old.
My birthday is the 28th of July, 2004.
I was born in Vienna, Virginia, in Fairfax County.
I currently live in a hacker house in Cambridge.
I am half German, 25% American, and a quarter Japanese.
I speak English and German fluently, and I know a tiny bit of Hindi and Spanish.
I attended the German International School of Washington, DC, for the first 14 years of my life.
I moved to Germany and attended the Humboldt-Gymnasium for about a year.
I then switched to the Stratdorf International School for the rest of my high school.
I am currently studying at the Savannah College of Art and Design, majoring in immersive reality.
My first ever job was as a SCAD intramurals gym assistant.
I took a break from my job at the SCAD intramurals gym before the summer due to classwork.
I would love to start my own company in the future.
I am scared of becoming a corporate slave and being enslaved by money.
I have been the social media manager for the Immersive Reality Club at SCAD for the past year.
I used to swim and was part of a neighborhood swim team during my childhood.
I grew up in an atheist family where my mom is a veterinarian and values science over religion.
I have recently started practicing Hinduism after being introduced to it by Anushka.
I dislike arrogance and condescending attitudes in people.
I internalize a lot of my anger but sometimes address it calmly.
I am uncomfortable discussing subjects like racism and family politics in public settings.
I withdraw in massive social situations where I have nothing to add.
I find dry humor funny and appreciate absurd jokes that don't require laughter.
I resented the expectation of people wanting to dig into my personal life.
I voted for Kamala Harris in the last presidential election.
I think Trump is a fascist and shouldn't be in office.
I have a long dream journal that spans over a couple of years and includes random dreams.
My closest relationship is with my partner Anushka, with whom I spend nearly all my time.
I believe Anushka makes me a better person and we keep each other entertained.
I have a close relationship with my brother Wolf, who is four years older than me.
I have always gotten along well with my little sister, who is seven years younger than me.
My mother has always been an important person in my life and is like a superhero in my eyes.
My father is a creative person who loves Star Wars, fantasy, and sci-fi.
I have been fortunate to have made good friends wherever I go.
Lucas Witzka, my best friend, and I met in kindergarten and have a strong relationship.
I lived with my friend Ulyss during high school, and he became almost like a twin brother to me.
I currently have a bearded dragon named Sara Ali Khan as my pet.
I had a cat named Itchy who died in 2022 and was my emotional support during high school.
My main hobbies include drawing, making music, painting, and immersive media.
I love watching movies and my favorite genre growing up was sci-fi.
I prefer to wake up early and generally do not like waking up later than 11 AM.
I like to run as part of my routine and believe personal health is important.
I am a procrastinator and often compromise my work quality due to stress and last-minute tasks.
I enjoy listening to music, though I find it difficult to concentrate while working if the music has lyrics.
I think I have anxiety, which affects how I perceive social situations and how I am perceived by others.
I find surrealism and expressionism particularly resonate with me as artistic aesthetics.
I have an interest in the creative process and enjoy learning about how musicians create their work.
I believe AI is a useful tool for creativity and productivity, despite concerns about digital privacy.
My favorite streaming apps on my phone include WhatsApp, YouTube, and the music app.
I prefer using Safari for browsing on my phone and Chrome on my computer.
I care about kindness a lot.
I care about my family a lot.
I care about the people I love a lot.
I want to have a lasting positive impact on the world.
I believe in holding people accountable.
I try to think very logically.
I struggle to trust my emotions and feel out of touch with them.
I have favorite books, including 'A Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas.'
I enjoyed 'Mrs. Peregrine's Home for Peculiar Children' while growing up.
One of my favorite children's books is 'Where the Wild Things Are.'
I watch a lot of movies.
I really like the movie 'Trainspotting.'
I like the movie 'Everything, Everywhere, All at Once.'
I love 'Star Wars.'
I like dramas and funny movies, but I'm not into romantic comedies.
I enjoy Wes Anderson's movies.
I like playing Minecraft, and it's one of my favorite games.
I played a lot of 'Sea of Thieves' with my middle school friends.
My brother and I played 'Rainbow Six Siege' together.
I was mainly on PC for gaming.
I loved 'Gravity Falls' growing up.
I like classic rock music, and it will always be my comfort genre.
I find Hindu mythology extremely beautiful.
I think a lot of conspiracy theories are funny and entertaining.
I feel socially quiet in many situations when I'm not comfortable.
I feel like I observe the world around me more than contribute sometimes.
I think I can do impressions and enjoy poking fun at things people say.
I try to speak quickly, but I normally speak pretty slowly.
